:"1600","1622":"1622","1567":"1567","1610":"1610","1544":"1544","1587":"1587","1565":"1565","1564":"1564","1563":"1563","1585":"1585","1584":"1584","1661":"1661","1562":"1562","14 September 1605":"14 September 1605","1607":"1607","1539":"1539","1605":"1605","1636":"1636","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England","Noseley, Leicestershire, England":"Noseley, Leicestershire, England","England":"England","Washington,Rhode Island":"Washington, Rhode Island, United States","Rhode Island, British Colonial America":"Rhode Island, British Colonial America","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Paybody","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Peabody  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Peabody","meanings":["English: nickname ‘peacock-body’, from Middle English <i>pe</i>, <i>pey</i>, <i>pay</i> (Old English <i>pēa</i>) ‘peacock’ + <i>body</i>, perhaps for a vain person who dressed ostentatiously. Compare   Pea  ,   Peacock  .","History: The prominent financier and philanthropist George Peabody was born 1795 in South Danvers, now Peabody, MA. His first ancestor in America was Francis Peabody, who emigrated from England in 1635 and settled at Topsfield, MA."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":6,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":8,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":22,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":24,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":37,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Paybody was born in 1563, in Noseley, Leicestershire, England, his father, William John Paybody, was 19 and his mother, Hannah Hale, was 24. He married Hannah Chute about 1580, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1610, in Rhode Island, British C